<title>Various foods and the protection of the rain for a fungus </title>
<summary><i>!haken, a food resembling &apos;Bushman rice&apos; is also used by Bushmen. (L VIII.-9. 6789 rev., note). That !haken above which a certain fungus grows is given to the old people. (L VIII.-11. 6945 rev.-6954 rev.). </i> The <i>!gu !gu</i> grows out of the <i>!haken</i> and is not eaten. The method of obtaining and administering <i>!haken</i> to the elderly (young people do not eat it) is also discussed.</summary><comments>1) This story is found in Book VIII-11</comments><date>9 June 1878</date><storypages>6945opp-6945v</storypages><category>The Rain and Rain&apos;s water</category><category>Custom and daily life</category><category>Plants and animals</category><author>|hanâ‰ kass'o (Klein Jantje) (VIII)</author><keyword><kw>rain</kw><subkw>and the collecting of different foods</subkw></keyword>
